narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I have learnt a lot about academic integrity and it is very helpful for my future career at Yale. By studying several real life examples, I have gained a better understanding of research ethics.
Please make this an online course... too boring to sit through lectures

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The course was mainly geared toward the computer science students taking it. It was not relevant to me as a math student.
Strength: - You can learn the basic knowledge for conducting research in America, which you should obey forever. Weakness: - No.
Strength: free pizza Weakness: content is dull, "course" is tedious

Pros: The examples we discussed in the class were really educative and I liked the interesting discussions. Cons: We could use a large classroom because there were always somebody sit outside the classroom.

I think the strength of the course was that it didn't try to tell us what's correct but introduced us scenarios that caused us to reason about the dilemma. I don't think there is any particular weakness I found for the course.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. This is mandatory for those who want to conduct research in America.
It's mandatory. But even otherwise, I think it's useful to develop an understanding of the responsibilities as students of computer science.
